{"type":"message","id":"ec69dfd8","parentId":"7c8bc50c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:59:41.917Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1qnlfe9r3tkt_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 145914\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 1 COMPLETE - Architecture analysis done\r\n2. CFI Compression Experiment done - yielded key insights about constant-format tokens\r\n3. Next experiment defined: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring (Strategy C)\r\n4. The formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- Run the hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring experiment\r\n- 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe \"Just applied\" mentions `research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` was just appended. This suggests the experiment might already be set up.\r\n\r\nBut I need to verify the current state and take the next concrete action. The next logical step from the CFI compression synthesis is to run the hybrid experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and what the current state is. I should look at:\r\n1. The CFI compression synthesis for the formula\r\n2. The existing experiment files to understand the pattern\r\n3. What needs to be done to run the hybrid experiment\r\n\r\nSince I'm Breakaway and each pulse is stateless, I need to look at what concrete action advances the goal. The goal is to run the hybrid experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me look at the experiment pattern from CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md or similar files to understand how to set up/run this experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, the user said \"Just applied: research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\" - this suggests there might already be some content there. But I need to understand the current state.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: Run the hybrid CFI×Freq experiment on the available pulses. I need to:\r\n1. Parse existing pulse data (pulse_*.md files)\r\n2. Extract CFI and freq for tokens\r\n\r\n\r\n3. Calculate hybrid score\r\n4. Evaluate performance (precision/recall against research trajectory)\r\n\r\nThe immediate next step is to implement the hybrid scoring mechanism. I'll write a script to parse token frequencies and CFI values from the pulse markdown files, then calculate the hybrid score using the specified formula. This will set up the groundwork for the 80/20 split evaluation.\r\n\r\nI'll focus on creating a Python or PowerShell script that can extract and process the token data efficiently, ensuring I can generate the precision/recall metrics needed to validate the hybrid approach.\r\n\r\nThe goal is to automate the experimental workflow, creating a reproducible method for testing the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring strategy across multiple pulse iterations.\r\n\r\nI'll design a modular script that can flexibly apply different threshold configurations, allowing precise comparison of binary versus hybrid scoring approaches. The implementation will focus on extracting token frequency and CFI data from pulse files, then systematically evaluating each strategy's performance.\r\n\r\nKey implementation steps involve creating a flexible token analysis framework that can handle variable threshold parameters, ensuring I can generate comprehensive performance metrics with minimal manual intervention.\r\n\r\nI'll develop a PowerShell script targeting the research directory, which will systematically extract token statistics and enable rapid experimental iteration across different token scoring strategies.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified the constant-format token problem (freq=160, CFI=1.00) but the hybrid scoring experiment (Strategy C) has been designed but not yet executed. The scoring formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` needs empirical validation.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/run_hybrid_experiment.ps1` - the execution script that will parse pulse files, calculate hybrid scores, and generate the precision/recall comparison data against the binary threshold approaches.\r\n\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n# Compares: hybrid_score vs binary thresholds (CFI≥0.7, CFI≥0.5)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$projectRoot = Split-Path (Split-Path $PSScriptRoot -Parent) -Parent\r\n$dataDir = Join-Path $projectRoot \"research\"\r\n$outFile = Join-Path $dataDir \"CFI_HYBRID_RESULTS.md\"\r\n\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path (Join-Path $projectRoot \"pulse_*\") -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime | Select-Object -First 200\r\n\r\n$allTokens = @{}\r\n$researchTokens = @{}  # ground truth: in pulses with research content\r\n\r\nforeach ($pf in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $pf.FullName -Raw\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\b\\w{4,}\\b') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    $uniqueTokens = $tokens | Sort-Object -Unique\r\n    \r\n    $isResearch = $content -match '(?:synthesis|insight|experiment|analysis|conclusion)'\r\n    foreach ($t in $uniqueTokens) {\r\n        if (-not $allTokens.ContainsKey($t)) {\r\n            $allTokens[$t] = @{freq=0; research=0}\r\n        }\r\n        $allTokens[$t].freq++\r\n        if ($isResearch) { $allTokens[$t].research++ }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate hybrid score: CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# For this experiment, use CFI proxy: research_freq/freq\r\n$results = foreach ($tok in $allTokens.Keys) {\r\n    $d = $allTokens[$tok]\r\n    $cfi = if ($d.freq -gt 0) { $d.research / $d.freq } else { 0 }\r\n    $freqScore = [Math]::Min(1, $d.freq / 120)\r\n    $hybrid = $cfi * $freqScore\r\n    [PSCustom\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:59:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774378781915}}
{"type":"message","id":"e3fdacbd","parentId":"ec69dfd8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:59:49.940Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse ran and the script created the experiment script. Now let me report the summary.","thinkingSignature":"81c196284fbb7996545042d31de9e8507e82719c7cb2952fa9e91ff991bac71b"},{"type":"text","text":"## Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 14:59 UTC\n\n**What happened:**\n1. **Synthesis completed** — the CFI compression analysis identified the constant-format token problem (freq=160, CFI=1.00 — tokens like \"pulse\" and \"mutation\" that appear constantly but carry no research signal)\n2. **Strategy C designed but not executed** — the hybrid formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)`压制高频无信号token，但尚未经验证\n3. **Mutation applied** — `research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` appended (experiment design doc)\n4. **Git commit** — 5 files changed, +218/-76 insertions\n\n**What was created (pending execution):**\n- `scripts/run_hybrid_experiment.ps1` — the script to run Strategy C vs binary threshold comparison on 200 historical pulses\n\n**Next step for the next pulse:** Execute the hybrid experiment script to get empirical precision/recall numbers for the three strategies."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2035,"output":240,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14520,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774378781917}}
